A potter works on a clay idol for Durga Puja festival in Dhaka, Bangladesh, on Sept. 28, 2020. Durga Puja is one of the largest Hindu festivals that involve worship of Goddess Durga symbolizing power and triumph of good over evil in Hindu mythology. Hindu artists are now busy preparing for the annual festival which will start from Oct. 22 this year.Photo:Xinhua 

